    {
      "id": "5a45c9c4_2891d4cc",
      "file_path": "packages/docker/src/main/docker/docker-files/scripts/bpmn-script/start-camunda-app.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 6,
      "message": "you can avoid unzipping war file if you add following in docker pom.xml while creating bpmn-infra image then you would only need to add COPY line in Dockerfile.so-bpmn-infra\n\n                     <dependencySet>\n                        <includes>\n                          <include>org.mariadb.jdbc:mariadb-java-client:jar</include>\n                        </includes>\n                      </dependencySet>",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3237,
        "name": "Waqas Ikram",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "waqas.ikram@est.tech",
        "username": "waqas.ikram"
      },
      "updated": "2021-09-08 11:05:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "7a3c814f_459864ca",
      "file_path": "packages/docker/src/main/docker/docker-files/scripts/bpmn-script/start-camunda-app.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 6,
      "message": "Hi Irshad, As Waqas suggested you can go to below path and do following changes :\n\nPath : so/packages/docker/pom.xml\n\n1. Replace current image with given content , just a little add on (\n<outputFileNameMapping>mariadb-java-client.jar</outputFileNameMapping>\n) here on top of waqas changes ,\n\n<image>\n              <name>${docker.image.prefix}/bpmn-infra</name>\n              <build>\n                <cleanup>try</cleanup>\n                <dockerFile>docker-files/Dockerfile.so-bpmn-infra</dockerFile>\n                <tags>\n                  <tag>${project.version}</tag>\n                  <tag>${project.version}-${maven.build.timestamp}</tag>\n                  <tag>${project.docker.latesttag.version}</tag>\n                </tags>\n                <assembly>\n                  <inline>\n                    <dependencySets>\n                      <dependencySet>\n                        <includes>\n                          <include>org.onap.so:mso-infrastructure-bpmn:war</include>\n                        </includes>\n                        <outputFileNameMapping>app.war</outputFileNameMapping>\n                      </dependencySet>\n                      <dependencySet>\n                        <includes>\n                          <include>org.mariadb.jdbc:mariadb-java-client:jar</include>\n                        </includes>\n                        <outputFileNameMapping>mariadb-java-client.jar</outputFileNameMapping>\n                      </dependencySet>\n                    </dependencySets>\n                  </inline>\n                </assembly>\n              </build>\n            </image>\n\n2. Go to Dockerfile.so-bpmn-infra and COPY below snippet :\n\nCOPY maven/mariadb-java-client.jar /camunda/lib\n\nI hope , I am not missing something important..",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6750,
        "name": "Mukesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mukeshsharma@est.tech",
        "username": "MukeshKumar"
      },
      "updated": "2021-09-08 12:01:20.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a45c9c4_2891d4cc",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
